# ScarCity — Project Handoff Summary

## What it is
Unity 6 (URP, 6000.3.6f1) 3D city game inspired by Dispatch. Top-down orthographic camera. STEM-teaching minigames triggered by crisis events on a city map. 3-minute timer, HP system, score = f(HP, time). Made by Grade 8 students.

## Scene Setup
- **ScarCity.unity** — main city scene. SimplePoly City asset pack. ~1044 prefab instances. Ortho camera at (400, 130, 140), 25° tilt, size 90. URP.
- **EarthquakeTriangulation.unity** — separate 2D minigame scene. Ortho camera at (0,0,-10).
- **GameOver.unity** — empty placeholder scene for game over state. To be built out later.
- All three scenes registered in Build Profiles.

## Scene Hierarchy (ScarCity)
```
ScarCity
├── Waypoints         (all traffic waypoints)
├── CarSpawner        (lane 1 entry)
├── CarSpawner (1)    (lane 2 entry)
├── City              (all visual city assets, SimplePoly pack)
├── CrisisSpawns
│   └── SpawnPoint    (one spawn point so far — add more)
└── [runtime] DontDestroyOnLoad
    ├── GameManager   (has GameManager.cs, MinigameBridge.cs, CrisisSpawner.cs)
    └── [Debug Updater] (from SimplePoly — ignore)
```

**Important:** GameManager, MinigameBridge, and CrisisSpawner are all on the **same GameObject**. Do NOT attach them to any other object (learned the hard way — they accidentally ended up on the Directional Light).

## Scripts Written

### Core Systems
- `GameManager.cs` — singleton, DontDestroyOnLoad, owns timer/HP/score. Score formula: `MAX_SCORE × (hp/maxHP) × (0.5 + 0.5 × timeLeft/totalTime)`. Defaults: `timeRemaining=180`, `currentHP=5`, `gameActive=true` (temp — revert to false when main menu is built). `citySceneName` must be `"ScarCity"`, `gameOverSceneName` must be `"GameOver"`.
- `CrisisSpawner.cs` — spawns CrisisMarkers at spawn points at escalating rate (20s→8s). Has one CrisisType configured: EarthquakeTriangulation. CrisisMarker prefab must be assigned in Inspector.
- `CrisisMarker.cs` — clickable popup with countdown timer. Uses **New Input System** (`Mouse.current.leftButton.wasPressedThisFrame` + `Physics.Raycast`) for click detection — NOT OnMouseDown. Has `Billboard.cs` attached so it always faces the camera. Needs a **SphereCollider** (not CircleCollider2D) on the root.
- `MinigameBridge.cs` — singleton on same GameObject as GameManager. `BeginMinigame()` pauses timer and loads minigame scene. `ReturnToCity(bool)` resumes timer and notifies the marker.
- `MinigameResult.cs` — abstract base class for all minigame controllers. Call `Succeed()` or `Fail()`.
- `CityHUD.cs` — drives timer label/bar, HP hearts, score. **Not yet placed in scene.**
- `Billboard.cs` — makes a GameObject always face the main camera via `LateUpdate`. Attached to CrisisMarker prefab root.

