## Key Technical Notes
- URP project — use **Sprite-Lit-Default** shader, not Sprites/Default
- **New Input System active** — OnMouseDown does NOT work in 2D scenes. Use IPointerDownHandler + Physics2DRaycaster + EventSystem. In 3D city scene, use `Mouse.current` + `Physics.Raycast` instead.
- CrisisMarker uses `TextMeshProUGUI` (not TextMeshPro) for its Canvas labels
- Minigame scenes are fully 2D, city scene is 3D — intentional and fine
- 1 Unity unit = 1 km in earthquake minigame
- Road surface Y≈0. Each road tile 20 units long, waypoints every ~60 units on straights
- `gameActive = true` is hardcoded for testing — revert to `false` when main menu is built
- Do not use ✓ or ✗ characters in result text — LiberationSans font doesn't support them

